INSERT INTO `gameList` (`gameID`, `gameName`, `gameRules`, `userID`, `gameDatestamp`) VALUES
(6, 'Soviet Foil', '		 					 					 			<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b>[A]</b></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> (the attacker) has a sword, </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b>[Z]</b></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> (the defender) may or may not have a sword, but they aren\'t allowed to do anything with it. Both are allowed to move around freely but </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b>[A]</b></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> can\'t change their guard. </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The game goes until <b>[A]</b> launches a single attack against <b>[Z]</b>.</span></p><ol><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">If </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b>[A]</b></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> hits they win.</span></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;\">If <span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b>[Z]</b></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> can dodge they win.</span></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">If the defender gets close enough to the boundary of the space they call \"reset\" and they return to the starting position. The defender should never feel that their ability to move quickly is limited by the space. This means that the attacker can\'t rush down the defender, they must bait them into coming in range. Adding a rule that the attacker can\'t cross their feet until the actual attack can also help reduce charging.</span></span></p>		 				 				 		', 1, '2021-04-27'),
(7, 'Fencer/Fighter', '		 					 					 					 					 						 						 						 						 						 			<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">The Fencer/Fighter game is an evolution of the\r\nSoviet Foil game, with additional options. In this case both have swords.&nbsp;<b>[A]</b>&nbsp;=\r\nattacker,&nbsp;<b>[Z]</b>&nbsp;= defender.<o:p></o:p></span></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;hits&nbsp;<b>[Z]</b>&nbsp;with\r\n     their attack before&nbsp;<b>[Z]</b>&nbsp;can back out.&nbsp;<b>[A]</b>&nbsp;wins.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;does\r\n     not hit anything with their attack.<b>&nbsp;[Z]</b>&nbsp;wins.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;hits&nbsp;<b>[Z]</b>\'s\r\n     sword with their attack, and [Z] can close distance within one step.&nbsp;<b>[Z]</b>&nbsp;wins.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;hits&nbsp;<b>[Z]</b>\'s\r\n     sword with their attack, and backs out before [Z] can close\r\n     distance.&nbsp;<b>[A]</b>&nbsp;wins.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ol><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Like the Soviet Foil game if the attacker\r\npressures the defender into the edge of the space the pair resets to the center\r\nwith no winner.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">\"Close distance\" means close enough\r\nto tag the shoulder with a hand, even if the tag doesn\'t make contact.</span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:black\"> Note that this rule applies after any blade contact, which does\r\nallow the Fencer to just tap and run away if the Fighter is getting too twitchy\r\nwith their sword.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>			 					 					 					 					 				 				 				 				 				 		', 1, '2021-11-16'),
(8, 'Direct Attack', '		 					 					 			<p>		 			Both the <b>[A]</b> (the attacker) and <b>[Z]</b> (the defender) are firm footed facing each other, not moving from their initial guard positions. <b>[A]</b> is allowed one attack (no feints or direction changes), within a limited set of parameters that are known to the defender*.</p><p>The response of <b>[Z]&nbsp;</b>is also specified ahead of time. The traditional version is a parry with no foot movement, but you could also specify that <b>[Z]</b> must back out without a parry, or that they may move and parry.\r\n</p><p>If <b>[A]</b> lands the attack twice in a row then <b>[Z]</b> will line up one step further than they have been positioning themselves. If <b>[Z]</b> succeeds twice in a row they should move one step closer. (If the first pass shows that they started at completely the wrong distance they should reposition without worrying about the \"move one step after two attacks\" rule.)</p><p>* The base version is something simple like \'right descending cut to the head\'. More options could be allowed for attacks, however at some point it becomes a variant drill rather than a rules tweak. The Direct Attack is an extremely simple scenario.</p>		 				 				 		', 1, '2021-04-27'),
(9, 'Indirect Attack', '		 					 			<p>		 			The game has a similar setup to the Direct Attack game, whereby both are facing each other firm footed waiting for the attacker to initiate. You can do the Indirect Attack with a cut, however it is designed, and works much better, as a thrusting game.</p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Both the <b>[A]</b> and <b>[Z]</b> are allowed to move their swords as much as they want while their feet don\'t move.</span></li><li>Once <b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[A]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> moves their feet to instigate their attack </span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[Z]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> should parry and begin running away.</span></li><li><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[A]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> can make as many attack attempts as they want until they reach the stop line, somewhere about 2-3 steps ahead of their starting point. (This is usually somewhere behind where </span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[Z]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> starts.)</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Win conditions:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>[A]</b> wins if they can land an attack. (Obviously.)</span></li><li><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[A]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> wins if </span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[Z]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> moves their feet while [A] remains planted.</span></li><li><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[Z]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> wins if they can parry successfully until they get out of range.</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Much like Direct Attack the distance should be increased or decreased to make the game balanced for the skill level of the two fencers.</span></p>		 				 		', 1, '2022-03-01'),
(10, 'Direct To Grapple', '		 					 					 					 			<p>		 			The setup for this is identical to the Direct Attack game, but with more options.<b> [A]</b> = attacker, <b>[Z]</b> = defender from the Direct Attack.</p><p>When <b>[A]</b> attacks<b> [Z]</b> may chose to defend by either (they lose if they do both):</p><ul><li>Parry without backing up</li><li>Back up without parrying.</li></ul><p>Which results in 3 outcomes:</p><ol><li>If the attack hits <b>[A]</b> wins.</li><li>If <b>[Z]</b> avoids any contact then they win.</li></ol><p>The third case is that <b>[Z]</b> parries successfully. In this case <b>[A]</b> may continue with a 1-H grappling action until:</p><ol><li><b>[A]</b> lands a valid scoring action, and thus wins.</li><li><b>[Z]</b> forces a stalemate, in which case they win. (Full control isn\'t necessary, just enough to make any onlookers think \"this isn\'t going anywhere fast\".)</li></ol><p>Once the grapple begins <b>[Z]</b> may move their feet, but can not run away. If either of the two deliberately breaks measure they lose.</p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-6b444729-7fff-50b6-c6d9-896aeaaa715e\"><div><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br></span></div></span><p>		 		</p>		 				 				 				 		', 1, '2022-01-29'),
(11, 'Tapping Game', '		 					 			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d73c44ab-7fff-addf-4b45-f58c8fbf69fe\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The roles are <b>[Tapper]</b> and <b>[Chaser]</b>. <b>[A</b></span></font><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b>ttacker]</b> moves around in a chambered position, <i>Vom Ta</i>g for a cut or Plow for a thrust, and <b>[Tapper]</b> has their sword centered and pointed online. Both move around waiting for the <b>[Tapper]</b>\'s cue, which is to bring their point down </span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">and</span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> back to tap twice on the ground <u>beside</u> them, and bring their sword back up in a parry. As soon as <b>[Chaser]</b> sees the point move offline they should begin their attack, trying to land the hit before <b>[Tapper]</b> can parry.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The attack should be predetermined and known to <b>[Tapper]</b>. The only question should be if they can get the sword up quickly enough to parry; trying to be tricky with the attack is not part of this game. <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tapper]</b> is allowed to take a small step back as they parry, but not run away while doing so.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tapper]</b> parries the attack then for the next round they increase the number of taps, so if they were able to parry with 2 taps they must do 3. If <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tapper]</b> fails to make the parry they will decrease the number of taps for the next round. In this way the game is self scaling for any differences in participant skill. A <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tapper]</b> who is much better than the <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Chaser]</b> might end up doing 5 taps, whereas if <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Chaser]</b> is more skilled <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tapper]</b> may be only able to get a single tap.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The last element of this game is that <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tapper]</b> is allowed to thrust <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Chaser]</b>, provided that they do so without moving their feet. This limits how close <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Chaser]</b> can get, they always have to be out of range. And, interestingly enough, means it\'s actually <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tapper]</b> who can bully <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Chaser]</b> around the space.</span></p></span>		 				 		', 1, '2021-12-12'),
(12, 'Measure Chicken', '		 					 					 					 			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-354da54e-7fff-7a82-939b-54b99c05ad9a\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:black\"=\"\">The game starts with a basic Defend the Wall setup: <b>[Z]</b>\r\n(the defender) can\'t move and <b>[A]</b> (the attacker) can only target above\r\nthe waist.</span><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0in\" type=\"disc\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l2 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:black\"=\"\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:black\"=\"\"> makes 6 attacks in a continuous motion, no backing out and\r\n     restarting allowed.</span><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:black\"=\"\">Possible outcomes:</span><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l0 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:black\"=\"\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:black\"=\"\"> lands 3 attacks, and wins (After the attacker has finished\r\n     their run the defender will tell them the number of hits they landed.)</span><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l0 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:black\"=\"\">[Z]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:black\"=\"\"> gets hit with 2 or fewer attacks and wins. (aka they parry 4\r\n     or more.)</span><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l0 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:black\"=\"\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:black\"=\"\"> throws an attack out of measure, which <b>[Z]</b> still\r\n     parries. On contact <b>[A]</b> stops moving and says \"call\",\r\n     which is a win for them.</span><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l0 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:black\"=\"\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:black\"=\"\"> throws an attack out of measure which <b>[Z]</b> lets go by\r\n     without contact. <b>[Z]</b> wins.</span><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ol><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">Other\r\nscenarios that come up:<o:p></o:p></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><ul style=\"margin-top:0in\" type=\"disc\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l1 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in\"><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">Feints are allowed but they\r\n     count as one of the 6 attacks.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l1 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in\"><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">Thrusts are allowed but you\r\n     can\'t \"call\" on a thrust.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l1 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">&nbsp;attacks\r\n     out of measure and <b>[Z]</b> goes to parry, but there is no contact. Call it a\r\n     draw.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l1 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">&nbsp;calls\r\n     on an attack which is a hand\'s width away from being in measure to hit <b>[Z]</b>\r\n     . Call it a draw.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:\r\n     l1 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">[A]</span></b><span style=\"font-family:\" arial\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">&nbsp;may\r\n     not call on any attack delivered with shortened arms, or else they could\r\n     just pull-in right before impact.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ul></span>		 				 				 				 		', 1, '2021-08-29'),
(13, 'Tower Defense', '		 					 			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-761ed831-7fff-8e91-ada6-520645aee0c1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In Tower Defense you have two roles. The first is a single person selected to be the <b>[Tower]</b>, (aka the attacker). Everyone else is a <b>[Mob]</b>, (aka the defenders). The <b>[Tower]</b> will be constrained to only move in a certain area, and a channel* will be created that the <b>[Mob]</b>s must move through while being attacked by the <b>[Tower]</b>. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">When a </span><b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Mob]</b><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\"> gets hit they will loudly yell \"good\". As soon as the current </span><b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Mob] </b><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">calls out, the next </span><b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Mob] </b><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">in line will start their run. If any of the </span><b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Mob]</b><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">s</span><b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\"> </b><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">makes it through the channel within the time limit the mob team wins, if the </span><b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tower] </b><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">manages to stop them all the tower wins. If you have enough space/people you can have two teams going head to head, with the \"captain\" of each being the tower defending the other team\'s mobs. First team to make it through wins.</span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; font-size: 11pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><u>Note</u>: for safety reasons the mobs </span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: underline; font-size: 11pt; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">must</span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; font-size: 11pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"> face the tower at all times, and may not turn away in order to run through the channel faster. This also means that they are constrained to move laterally while defending.</span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">*The exact geometry isn\'t important, and will likely depend on your training space. The important part is there is a narrow stretch that the mobs must run through while being attacked by the <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tower]</b>. The channel should be narrow enough that the mobs are forced into attacking distance of the <b style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">[Tower]</b>, but wide enough they aren\'t standing on top of each other. Typically leg shots are banned, but if you have a wide enough channel it can be fun to mix it up.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><br></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><br></p></span>		 				 		', 1, '2021-12-08'),
(14, 'Breakout', '		 					 			<div><u>Win Condition</u>: Land a thrust</div><div><br></div><ul><li>Starts out like the direct attack drill for a thrust, with <b>[A]</b> being the attacker and <b>[Z]</b> being the defender.</li><li>Once <b>[A]</b> initiates <b>[Z]</b> both parries and backs up.</li><li><b>[A]</b> can pursue and do as many thrusts/feints as they can manage.</li><li>Once <b>[Z]</b> crosses their line with both feet the roles switch and they become the attacker. <b>[A]</b> must defend and run away.</li><li>When <b>[A]</b> crosses their line the roles switch back again. Keep going back and forth until someone gets hit. (Could be on the very first direct attack.)</li></ul>		 				 		', 1, '2022-10-11'),
(15, 'Flushing Out', '		 			<p><i>(Extrapolation of Direct Attack w/ Prep. )</i></p><p><u>Initial Conditions</u>:</p><ul><li>The<b> [Z]</b> stands in a fixed position between the Initiation and Stop Lines.&nbsp;</li><li>Before an \'initiation\'&nbsp;<b>[A]</b> can move behind the initiation line freely and move their sword however they want.&nbsp;</li><li>The <b>[Z]</b> can\'t move their feet, but can move their sword freely. Much like in the direct attack they should go closer/further to the initiation line depending on who is winning more.</li></ul><p><u>Actions</u>:</p><ul><li>If <b>[A]</b> crosses the Initiation Line or does any aggressive blade motion/attack (even from behind the line) they will be considered to have \"initiated\".</li><li><b>[A]</b> can not cross the stop line. They can stand right at the line and continue attacking if the defender is still in range.</li></ul><p><u>Win Conditions</u>:</p><ol><li>If <b>[A]</b> can hit the defender they win</li><li>If <b>[Z]</b> can back out behind the stop line without being hit they win. Far enough out of range that <b>[A]</b> can\'t reach them even at the stop line.</li><li>If <b>[Z]</b> moves their feet, and <b>[A]</b> never initiates then <b>[A]</b> wins.</li><li><b>[Z]</b> may step forward and attack. <b>[A]</b> always has priority.</li></ol><p><br></p><p>#3 means that <b>[Z]</b> is able, and encouraged, to pre-empt the attacker in running away. <b>[Z]</b> should start running when <b>[A]</b> has mentally committed to attacking and won\'t abort even if they see them running away.</p><p>#4 Means that <b>[Z]</b> can just attack if <b>[A]</b> is getting too cute and leaving themselves exposed on the approach. <b>[Z]</b> also has the option of running away past the stop line if they attack and it fails (but they don\'t get hit.) Any double/afterblow goes to <b>[A]</b>.&nbsp;</p>		 		', 1, '2022-10-11'),
(16, 'Cat on a Hot Tin Roof', '		 			<div><b>[Cat]</b> and <b>[Stoic]</b> roles.&nbsp;</div><ul><li><b>[Cat]</b> is not allowed to stop moving, and not allowed to hold any guard position. (aka constantly moving)</li><li><b>[Stoic]</b> has one foot planted and can only move the other. They must wait in their chosen guard and can\'t switch.</li></ul>		 		', 1, '2022-09-22'),
(17, 'Chamber Game', '<div>Both fighter start a little bit outside the range they can hit the head without moving, and plant their back foot. The back foot is not allowed to move, the front can move freely but not pass behind the rear.</div><div><br></div><div>Only valid targets are cuts to the the hand/wrist and the head. Hits to the hand have priority over hit to the head.</div>', 1, '2022-09-03'),
(18, 'Steel vs Paw', '		 			<div><b>[A]</b> has a sword, <b>[Z]</b> is unarmed.</div><div><br></div><ul><li><b>[A]</b> wins by thrusting <b>[Z]</b> in the torso. (If it\'s too unbalance for the fencers doing it you can change it to head thrust only)</li><li><b>[Z]</b> wins by getting close enough to tag <b>[A]</b>\'s shoulder.</li></ul><div>A thrust to the hands or arms of <b>[Z]</b> is not a scoring action, but resets the action (aka: <b>[Z]</b> can\'t run in while tanking a thrust to a protected target). <b>[Z]</b> is allowed any contact with the side of the blade they want, but no grabbing.</div>		 		', 1, '2022-09-03'),
(20, 'Chain Chomp', '<p>		 					 			Both fencers have their left foot \'in the hole\' (<i>grubline</i> style). The foot placements are far enough such that if one moves as far back as possible and one moves as far forward as possible they could just barely hit each other throwing for extreme range. Other than not moving the foot in the hole, regular sparring rules apply.		 				 		<br><br></p><p>(Chain chomp = these dudes)</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"width: 421px;\" data-filename=\"image.png\"><br></p>', 1, '2022-08-21'),
(21, 'In-and-Out Fighter', '		 			<div><i>Based around asymmetric weapon lengths (eg Dussak vs Singlestick) but can be done with similar.</i></div><div><b>[In]</b> Fighter - Short weapon</div><div><b>[Out]</b> Fighter - Long weapon</div><div><br></div><div><b>[Out]</b> wins on a clean hit, but an afterblow or double is a complete negation.</div><div><b>[In]</b> wins on a clean hit, or if they can tag the shoulder of the out fighter with their hand.</div>		 		', 1, '2022-07-29'),
(22, 'Draw To The Button', '<div>Create a \'ring\', with starting positions and a center mark. Each fighter starts at the starting position.</div><div>The timer decided on a time between 3-6 seconds, and doesn\'t tell anyone else.</div><div><br></div><div>Timer yells \'go\', and there are 3 possible outcomes:</div><ol><li>Time elapses, and the individual with their body closest to the center gets +2 points</li><li>One fencer gets a clean hit and is awarded +1 point</li><li>Double hit, both get -2 points</li></ol><div><br></div><div>Grappling is allowed, however no points will be awarded for being \'closer\' to the center unless it is very clear one is dominating the space. All other timeouts will result in a victor being awarded, even if it\'s only a few cm.</div>', 1, '2022-07-30'),
(23, 'Curling', '		 					 					 			<div>One fencer starts with \"<i>the hammer</i>\".</div><ul><li>Hit by fencer with hammer: 3 pts</li><li>Hit by fencer w/o hammer: 1 pt</li></ul><div><i>Hammer</i> starts with whoever lost the last exchange.</div><div>Every time the blades make contact the <i>Hammer</i> transfers to the other fighter.</div><div><br></div><div>Fight to 9 points. (or whatever).</div><div>(\"The hammer\" is a term from the sport of curling, awarded to the team which lost the last round. No actual hammers are required to play this game, and I\'m not responsible for anyone\'s safety if you elect to go that route.)</div>		 				 				 		', 1, '2022-05-27'),
(24, 'From Circle to 60', '		 					 			<div>Both fencers circle each other at a distance. They each have a unique verbal cue.</div><div>An outside observer yells the cue for one of the fencers (who now becomes <b>[A]</b>).</div><div><br></div><ul><li><b>[A]</b> has to launch an attack and hit <b>[Z]</b> before <b>[Z]</b> can back out of range.</li><li>If <b>[Z]</b> backs out of range they win, if <b>[A]</b> hits they win.</li></ul>		 				 		', 1, '2021-08-25'),
(25, 'Thrust Toggle', '		 					 			<p>One fighter can only thrust, the other can only defend. No grappling allowed, but I typically allow half swording if someone really wants to.</p><ol><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Every 5 seconds someone yells \"SWITCH\" and the roles change, but action is continuous.&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Fight goes on until someone lands a thrust.&nbsp;</span></li></ol><p>(Establish some sort of area so that the defender can\'t just run away the whole time.)<br></p><div><br></div>		 				 		', 1, '2022-11-07'),
(26, 'Deep vs Shallow - On The March', '		 					 					 			<div><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Two roles, <b>[Deep]</b> and <b>[Shallow]</b>, Both on a linear path facing each other, <b>[Shallow]</b> can only back up (or stand their ground), <b>[Deep]</b> can move freely forward or back. Win conditions:</span></div><div><br></div><ul><li><b>[Deep]</b> Win: Lands thrust to torso or a cut/thrust to the head. They also win if they can get their opponent tied up in a grapple.</li><li><b>[Shallow]</b> Win: Lands an attack to the arms or leg bellow the knee.</li><li><b>[Deep]</b> Win: <b>[Shallow]</b> backs up across a stop line placed several meters behind their initial position.</li><li><b>[Deep]</b> Win: <b>[Shallow]</b> steps forward <u>and does not land a scoring hit in the process</u>. <b>[Shallow]</b> is allowed to step forward with an attack, but if it does not hit they lose. (similar to a sacrifice throw.)</li></ul>		 				 				 		', 1, '2022-11-07'),
(27, 'Get to the Chopper', '		 					 			<p><b>[Z]</b> stands in a fixed position and can not move their feet (like defend the wall they can not attack, only defend). A slice to the arms by <b>[Z]</b> is not a scoring action, but it is allowed to inhibit <b>[A]</b>.<br><b>[A]</b> can move freely and starts a few steps away from <b>[Z]</b>. They can only attack the head with cuts. (Feints are allowed and encouraged.)<br><br>A timer will shout \"Go!\" when the game begins. The two outcomes are:</p><ul><li><b>[A]</b>&nbsp;wins by managing to land a cut to <b>[Z]</b>\'s&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">head before the time expires.</span></li><li><b>[Z]</b> wins by not being hit before the time runs out.</li></ul><p>If <b>[A]</b> wins then the time interval will be shortened by 1 second for the next round. If <b>[Z]</b> wins the time interval will be lengthened by 1 second for the next round. (5 seconds is a good mid-range to start everyone at.)<br><br></p>		 				 		', 1, '2022-11-13'),
(28, 'Fechten am Grubline', '		 			<p>Fencing version of <i>das Grubline</i>.&nbsp;</p><ul><li><b>[A]</b> has their foot \"in the hole\". One foot must remain planted (but can rotate) and the other can move freely. They lose if this foot moves off it\'s place.</li><li><b>[Z] </b>is hopping on one foot, but can move freely. They lose if the other foot touches the ground, but are allowed to put it down as part of an attack that hits. (This is like a sacrifice throw in wrestling. You get the point if it works, you lose if it doesn\'t.)</li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Other than the footwork constraints it is sparring as normal.</span></p>		 		', 1, '2022-11-13'),
(29, 'HEMA Chess', '<ol><li>Throw down a big grid of squares approximately 1m wide. Grid should be at least 5 x 5. (Big enough squares that you can stand in a fencing stance, but also small enough you can move into the next square with a single step.</li><li>Each player gets randomly assigned a piece. This piece defines how they can move, just like in chess.</li><li>Other than the weird movement restrictions normal sparring rules apply. Go to first hit.</li></ol><p><u>Movement Definitions</u></p><p><b>Players do not have to stop in each square and may move fluidly. </b>They should also adjust their orientation so they are always facing the opposing player. They, however, must always be either in a square or moving between two squares. You may not step into one square and then move to another square before entering the first square. Examples:</p><ul><li>You can not do an attack on a lunge, because you are ending straddling two squares. Unless the lunge-gather is done without interruption.</li><li>The rook can move diagonally forward-left by moving fully to the right square, then fully forward. They must pass through the intervening square completely.</li></ul><p>Small foot faults are ignored (as it would be lame to interrupt the game every time.) In addition if the bishop runs backwards several squares and ends up slightly off-angle, and a square over, it isn\'t a big deal. As long as people are trying to do the correct thing.</p><p><u>Piece Definitions</u></p><ul><li>Pawn: Can only move forward. If they get to opposing end they end they become a queen.</li><li>Bishop: Can only move along diagonals.</li><li>Knight: Can move in the L shape a knight moves in chess (look it up). They must do it as a leaping action, but if there is a foot touch down in the middle by shorter or less athletic player it is allowed.</li><li>Rook: Can only move in 4 directions.</li><li>Queen: Can move in all 8 directions.</li><li>King: Can move in all 8 directions, but can not move into any of the 8 squares adjacent to the other player. (A king can\'t move into checkmate.)</li></ul>', 1, '2022-12-15'),
(30, 'Soviet Chicken', '<p>Fencers start out of measure and must move forward continuously. They may not back up or stop moving. The only allowed action is a direct cut to the head.</p><p>A fencer scores if they attack and hit, or if their opponent attacks and falls short. Parries are not allowed.</p><p>If both fencers attack, award the point to whoever initiated their attack first. If the attacks are simultaneous, there is no score.<br></p>', 13, '2022-12-18');
INSERT INTO `gameList` (`gameID`, `gameName`, `gameRules`, `userID`, `gameDatestamp`) VALUES
(31, 'Counted Parries', '		 			<p style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"></p><p style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"></p><ul></ul><p></p><ul><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">[A] is the attacker, [B] is the defender.</span></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Switch roles on each exchange, continuing until one fencer reaches 5 points.</span></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-1c91965d-7fff-167f-a02a-9759ddef2a01\">Fencers may only score when it\'s their turn. Hits made during the opponent\'s turn are ignored.</span></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-85db5f2d-7fff-3c56-2529-4a2ca00a5efc\">[A] takes the first turn -- they can make two blows, and each hit is worth 1 point.</span></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-4dcd35f7-7fff-64bb-e2ff-8e38f99850ca\">After [A] has delivered their blows, [B] gets one blow. If it hits, it\'s worth 2 points. [B] still gets a turn even if one or both of [A]\'s attacks hit.</span></li></ul><p style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-4dcd35f7-7fff-64bb-e2ff-8e38f99850ca\">An exchange may end early if:</span></p><ul><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-4ee9d7a9-7fff-a873-efbb-abc351d6b0a9\">Fencers break measure any time after the first blow has been delivered.</span></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9669c3d4-7fff-e9ba-faff-8b3074e3bc6f\">Fencers come to a clinch or otherwise get tangled up</span></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9669c3d4-7fff-e9ba-faff-8b3074e3bc6f\">[B] retreats out of the ring</span></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ec36d584-7fff-1389-2c73-ffd8c03c6db5\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9669c3d4-7fff-e9ba-faff-8b3074e3bc6f\">Any contact with the opponent\'s sword or body counts as a blow (\"anything that makes a noise\" is a good rule of thumb when judging). </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Feints, or actions in the bind which maintain blade contact, don\'t count as blows. An action which makes blade contact and then hits the opponent in a single motion is counted as one blow. This does means that you can use beats and aggressive parries to proactively disrupt and take away your opponent\'s blows.</span></p>		 		', 13, '2022-12-18'),
(32, 'Bone Game', '		 					 			<ol><li>Both fighters start holding the sword (try having different grips for starting positions every time.)</li><li>Normal sparring. Aka, keep going until someone generates a point scoring action*.</li></ol><p><i>*<u>Examples</u>: plant the point on your opponent, disarm them and land a cut, bop them with the pommel if they aren\'t paying attention.&nbsp;</i></p><p>(Game is like two dogs fighting over a bone.)</p><div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"width: 344px;\" data-filename=\"image.png\"><br></div>		 				 		', 1, '2022-12-19'),
(33, 'Long Division', '<p>Put tape on the sword to clearly divide the blade into 3 parts.</p><ol><li>Thrusts are only scoring actions using the far third (weak).</li><li>Cuts are the only scoring action using the middle third (middle).</li><li>Slices are the only scoring action using the close third (strong).</li></ol><p>Borderline actions to be handled by the judges discretion.</p>', 14, '2021-11-30'),
(34, 'King in the Hole', '<ol><li>Mark a \'hole\' on the floor around 1ft in diameter</li><li>One fencer is the king. They place one foot in the hole and lose if they remove it</li><li>The other fencer is the challenger and can move freely.&nbsp;</li><li>The king wins if they can land a clean hit, or on any double-hit or afterblow</li><li>The challenger wins if they can land a clean hit, or if they can force the king to move their foot out of the hole</li><li>There is no limit to the afterblow tempo, challenger just has to get out of distance of the king</li></ol>', 14, '2022-07-28'),
(35, 'Day and Night', '<p>Mark or otherwise denote start lines and back lines on both sides of the gym. Make sure there\'s a decent runoff behind the back lines</p><ul><li>Participants on one side of the gym are \"day\" and the other side are \"night\"</li><li>Start on start lines. Both participants maneuver freely as they wish</li><li>Leader calls out \"day\" or \"night\" whenever they see fit</li><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">If your side is called, you retreat to get away behind your back line, while the opponent tries to catch you</span></li><li>If you get away safely you win. If you are caught, they win</li><li>Reset and play again</li></ul><p>Normally crossover steps are banned for both participants</p>', 14, '2022-10-14'),
(36, 'Made You Jump', '<ol><li>Fencers start at advance-lunge distance or so. Pick a leader.&nbsp;</li><li>The leader takes three steps forward, at any pace/size they want (within reason). The follower has to follow those steps exactly, step for step.&nbsp;</li><li>The leader wins a point if they make the follower take a step without taking their own. They have to keep their feet planted while doing this, but can use body feints etc.</li><li>After the third step, the roles swap and the follower becomes the leader. </li></ol><p>Swap back and forth until bored/tired.</p>', 14, '2022-11-19'),
(37, 'War/Skirmish', '		 			<ul><li>Either fencer can score by attacking and hitting</li><li>If an attack is parried, the defender becomes [A] and the attacker becomes [B].<br></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \" chivo\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 400;=\"\" font-style:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant:=\"\" text-decoration:=\"\" none;=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-0db5c86c-7fff-7b1b-abbd-d864ed4c212e\">[A] scores by making a touch while keeping blade contact.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \" chivo\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 400;=\"\" font-style:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant:=\"\" text-decoration:=\"\" none;=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-0db5c86c-7fff-7b1b-abbd-d864ed4c212e\">[B] scores by making a touch without blade contact.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \" chivo\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 400;=\"\" font-style:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant:=\"\" text-decoration:=\"\" none;=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-0db5c86c-7fff-7b1b-abbd-d864ed4c212e\">If [B] attacks and falls short, it\'s a point for [A].</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \" chivo\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 400;=\"\" font-style:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant:=\"\" text-decoration:=\"\" none;=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-0db5c86c-7fff-7b1b-abbd-d864ed4c212e\">You can be somewhat forgiving about the blade contact in either direction: e.g. if [A] thrusts from the bind but loses blade contact at the last moment, or [B] cuts around and there\'s some incidental contact as [A] tries to parry, both of those should score.</span></p>		 		', 13, '2022-12-19');
INSERT INTO `gameList` (`gameID`, `gameName`, `gameRules`, `userID`, `gameDatestamp`) VALUES
(38, 'Hang, Don\'t Suck', '		 					 			<div><u>Rules</u></div><ul><li>One person starts in <i>high vom tag</i>, the other in <i>alber</i>.</li><li>They must alternate hanging parry counters (an endless high-low parry cycle.</li></ul><p><u>Win Conditions</u><i>(ends the current cycle)</i></p><ul><li>Hit their opponent in the head, shoulder, or hands is a win.</li><li>The cuts must come down at a descending angle. <u>An illegal cut is a loss</u>.</li><li>Parries must be made with the hilt higher than the point. <u>Parrying with the point up is a loss</u>.</li><li>If you pause or break the cycle you lose.</li></ul><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"width: 327px; height: 224.777px;\" data-filename=\"image.png\"><br></p>		 				 		', 1, '2022-12-19');
INSERT INTO `gameList` (`gameID`, `gameName`, `gameRules`, `userID`, `gameDatestamp`) VALUES
(39, 'Ring Around The Rosie', '		 					 					 			<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Setup some area of about 4m in diameter for the teams to run\r\naround the outside of - no one is allowed to cross into the center.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Each team has a&nbsp;<b>[Runner]</b> and a&nbsp;<b>[Chaser]</b>, who are on the\r\nopposite sides of the course. On the call of \"go\" each&nbsp;<b>[Runner]</b> must run\r\n<u>backwards</u> as fast as they can to catch up to their counterpart <b>[Runner]</b>. If they\r\nmanager to catch up their team wins.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">The difficulty is that the opposite team\'s <b>[Chaser]</b> will be attacking the\r\n<b>[Runner]</b> the whole time.&nbsp; Should the <b>[Runner]</b> get hit (ie: fail to parry) they must come to a full stop before they can start\r\nrunning backwards again. (The <b>[Runner]</b> must face the <b>[Chaser]</b> at all times.)&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">The <b>[Runner]</b> does not need to, and should not, ever try to let\r\nthe <b>[Chaser]</b> catch up. They should be trying to open a gap\r\nbetween them and the <b>[Chaser]</b> to enable them to focus on running without\r\nparrying.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p></o:p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"Catching up\" to the other side is called by an outside observer,\r\nusually when the <b>[Runner]</b> is close enough to their teammate that the observer\r\nthinks a collision might be possible if it continues. (The winner is pretty\r\nobvious well before the two contact each other.)</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"width: 353.5px; height: 272.454px;\" data-filename=\"image.png\"><o:p></o:p></p>		 				 				 		', 1, '2022-08-24');
INSERT INTO `gameList` (`gameID`, `gameName`, `gameRules`, `userID`, `gameDatestamp`) VALUES
(40, 'Mouse On The Chessboard', '		 			<p>This uses the chess board and movement rules from HEMA Chess.</p><ul><li><b>[Mouse]</b> is just and out-of-place rodent dropped on a cruel chess board<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">, and has no movement restrictions other than not being able to leave the chess board (keep at least one foot in, just like tournament ring-out rules). Also they don\'t have any weapon or way to defend themselves.</span></li><li><b>[Knight]</b> must move using the HEMA Chess rules (for a knight piece), and they are only allowed to thrust.</li></ul><p>This is a keep-alive game for the <b>[Mouse]</b>. Win conditions can be either:</p><ol><li>Head-to-head: Both play one role as each, whoever was able to stay alive longer as <b>[Mouse]</b> wins.</li><li>Time Threshold: After 20 seconds the timer yells \"Free\" and if <b>[Mouse]</b> can get off the board without getting hit they win. (Adjust the time based on the size of the board you\'re working with. 5 x 5 is probably the absolute minimum board size that works.</li></ol>		 		', 1, '2022-12-21'),
(41, 'Two-handed foil', '<div>Fence a 5 point match where the only scoring action is the thrust to the chest. Half-swording and wrestling actions, be it body slams, throws, or arm grabs, are banned. Arbitrate double hits using right of way.</div>', 7, '2022-12-22'),
(42, 'La longue pe', '		 			<p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Fence a 5 point match where the only scoring action is the thrust to the chest. Half-swording and wrestling actions, be it body slams, throws, or arm grabs, are banned.</span></p><div><br></div>		 		', 7, '2022-12-22'),
(43, 'Feints, damned feints', '		 			<p>Consider the following progression:</p><ol><li>An attacker in a thrusting guard faces a defender in <i>vom tag</i>. The attacker can only advance, the defender can only retreat. The attacker wins if they hit the defender with a thrust to the chest or (figuratively) push the defender out of bounds. The defender wins if they can firmly bind the opponent\'s blade.</li><li>The defender now only wins if they can touch the attacker with their off-hand; parrying is no longer enough. They are allowed a single passing step to do so. The attacker is allowed to retreat once their thrust has been parried; if they manage to leave measure without being touched, they can resume their advance and attack again.</li><li>The defender is now allowed to counter-attack with a cut, but can\'t move forward as they do so. The attacker still wins if there is a double.</li><li>The attacker is now allowed to aim for the defender\'s hands and arms with a thrust.</li></ol><div><br></div>		 		', 7, '2022-12-22'),
(44, 'Primo tempo', '		 			<ol><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">An attacker stands in a thrusting guard and moves back and forth with advances and retreats. The defender stands in an open guard from which they can counter-thrust or beat the thrust to the ground, and is free to move however they want. Both fencers try to hit their opponent with a thrust to a deep target. The attacker is only allowed to perform straight thrusts or disengages; they cannot parry nor perform additional footwork as they strike, but have priority if a double hit happens.</span></li><li>The attacker is now allowed to lunge as they strike.</li><li>The defender is now allowed to parry and riposte with cuts.</li><li>The attacker is now allowed to pass or flche as they strike.</li></ol>		 		', 7, '2022-12-22'),
(45, 'Bullshido!', '		 					 					 					 					 					 			<ol><li>Agree upon a scope for the sources to be used. <i>Examples: \"RDL glosses\", \"Meyer dussak and rapier\", \"Any longsword source\", etc</i></li><li>Fighters spar until a valid scoring hit is landed. (This is no different from normal sparring, and the source chosen doesn\'t need to influence the sparring.)</li><li>Whoever lands the hit decides if they want to be the <i>Sensei</i> or the <i>Student</i>.</li><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">The<i> Sensei </i>explains the exchange in as much technical detail as possible, using only the terms and framework of the sources in scope.</span></li><li>The <i>Student </i>can either chose to <b>Accept</b>&nbsp;that the explanation matches the source, or call <b>Bullshido!</b> if they think the Sensei is making something up. (They have to yell \"Bullshido!\", not just say it normally.)</li><li>If the <i>Student</i> is correct they win, if they make the wrong call the <i>Sensei</i> wins.</li></ol><p>You will need copies of the source around and an <i>Arbitrator</i> to decide. Once the <i>Arbitrator</i> has made a judgement it is final and uncontestable. (Until maybe at the bar after practice.)</p>		 				 				 				 				 				 		', 1, '2022-12-24'),
(46, 'Gustav\'s Gambit', '<p>You need a marked central line and end lines for this game. Fencers start behind the end lines.&nbsp;</p><p>To start with, fencers should compete to arrive at the central line first, whoever crosses it with one foot first will be the attacker, and the other the defender. If both fencers cross it at the same time (or in such a way that it is difficult to tell who crossed first), they need to return to their start line and reach the center again, until one has decisively crossed first.</p><p>The attacker may attack as many times as they want against the defender. The defender cannot attack, but only parry. If the defender touches the blade once AND reaches their back line, the roles switch, and this goes on and on until a hit is achieved. Fencers then reset, and restart the game.</p>', 6, '2022-10-12'),
(47, 'Ruinous Remise', '<p>Fencers start and may both try to hit each other with a direct attack.</p><p>If one fencer chooses to parry, the attacker wins on completing a renewed attack, even if it is parried or voided, or if the fencer is hit while doing it. The parrying fencer wins if they can physically disrupt the renewed action from taking place.</p><p>Double hits on the attack are thrown out, so are double hits if both fencers assumed they were doing the initial attack.</p>', 6, '2022-07-18'),
(48, 'Crossed Crowns', '		 			<p>Fencers meet in close range with hands/hilt touching and at mask height. Goal is to land a touch.&nbsp;</p><p>Fencers may not step back, shove so that the other fencer is pushed or unbalanced, and they can\'t wrestle at the sword and must have both hands on hilt.&nbsp;</p><p>Touches made with the strong is invalid. In case of a double, the higher touch wins.&nbsp;</p><p>Can be done unjudged but a third person to call fence is helpful&nbsp;</p>		 		', 6, '2022-05-18'),
(49, 'Chicken\'s Wrath', '<p>Fencers in High guards. Goal for each is to land a touch. Both fencers get one attack, and may step forwards but not backwards</p>', 6, '2021-11-11'),
(50, 'The RDL', '<p>Fencing, but must temporarily gain control in grappling to cash score (e.g hitting two times only applies if you manage to grab and control opponents blade). Fencers can choose to cash in at any time. Failed attempts reset their scoring.</p>', 6, '2021-04-24'),
(51, 'Finnish Chicken', '		 			<p>Both fencers start out of distance in right <i>Vom Tag</i>. As they move closer to each other they are allowed to pick one of two actions:</p><ol><li>Direct cut to the head from the right*.</li><li>Parry against the cut to the head from the right**.</li></ol><p>This can be played with either free movement, or starting a fair distance out of range and not allowing any retreat.</p><p><i>*If they both attack, look at who was moving forward and who was standing still. In just about all cases one person didn\'t move their feet and thus were clearly attacking in response to their opponent instead of parrying. Auto-lose.</i></p><p><i>**If you can\'t tell if someone was parrying or attacking it is also an auto-lose. Make it clearer. This isn\'t sparring, it\'s a game with rules that you need to follow.</i></p>		 		', 1, '2021-04-09'),
(52, 'Sabre Box Game', '		 			<p>Fencers start at lines about 4 meters from each other, the space between the lines will be called\"the box\". A ref says \"ready, fence\" and the fencers step into the box and may attack each other anywhere above the belt. A double goes to whoever has attack priority. Parrying is not allowed, but a fencer may lock out the other person\'s attack with their counterattack. If a fencer leaves the box, the other fencer gets a point. First to five points wins.</p>		 		', 5, '2022-05-08'),
(53, 'Five Point Leg Game', '<div>Normal fencing match to 15 points.</div><ul><li>All hits that don\'t land on the legs are worth 1 point. (Hip is not the leg)</li><li>Clean leg hits are worth 5.</li><li>Leg hits which are a double or afterblow award the other fencer 2 points. (0 for whoever hit the leg)</li></ul>', 5, '2022-04-26'),
(54, 'Tall vs Short', '		 			<p>A is the \"shorter fencer\" is the\"taller fencer\" (either can be either height, that is just the convention of the roles). Both fencers start in a point high shoulder guard. B stands in one spot, A starts from out of distance and is free to move closer or further as they please. At any time, either side can attack only with a downward cut to the head, which the other side may attempt to parry riposte to any target above the belt. Counterattacks and renewals do not count. If the parry riposte is parried, then the person who parries it wins. Goal for both sides is to land a hit or to parry a riposte.</p>		 		', 5, '2022-03-14'),
(55, 'Grab or Go', '<p>This is a longsword game, it will not work as-is with 1h weapons.</p><p>A fencer can only score if:</p><ul><li>With a 1h attack if they are engaging their opponent in a grapple.</li><li>If their opponent has only 1h on the sword.</li></ul>', 5, '2022-01-23'),
(56, 'Uberlauffen Game', '		 			<ul><li><b>A</b> must start in point high guard, may only attack upper openings, and has priority on the initial attack.</li><li><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">B</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> must start in a low guard, and has priority on the parry riposte.</span></li><li>If the exchange continues past the parry riposte, a double is a wash.</li></ul>		 		', 5, '2021-12-12'),
(57, 'HVT vs Alber', '		 			<p><b>A</b> must start in <i>High Vom Tag</i> and <b>B</b> in <i>Alber.</i></p><ol><li><b>A</b> wins by landing a touch of any kind.</li><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>B</b> wins by establishing blade contact.</span></li></ol><p><b>B</b> may attempt an attack in prep, but <b>A</b> gets priority in a double.</p>		 		', 5, '2021-11-03'),
(58, 'Rock Paper Scissors', '<p>Each player has 3 options: </p><ol><li>long oberhaw to head</li><li>short oberhaw to hands</li><li>zwerhaw.</li></ol><p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Zwerhaw has priority over head attack, hand attack has priority over zwerhaw, and head attack has priority over hand attack.&nbsp;</span></p><p>(Zwer =&nbsp; rock, Hand = paper, Head = scissors)</p>', 5, '2021-10-07'),
(59, 'The Hammer', '<p>Fence to 6 points. </p><p>Flip a coin to decide who starts with priority. (<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Whoever has priority gets the point in the case of a double.)</span></p><ol><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">The fencer with priority receives 2 points upon a clean hit instead of 1. </span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">They still receive 1 point if their priority is used in a double. </span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Whenever there is a double, priority switches to the other fencer.</span></li></ol>', 5, '2021-09-08'),
(60, 'Priority Roulette ', '<p>Flip a coin to decide who starts with priority. </p><p>Fence to 5 points. </p><ul><li>Whoever has priority gets the point in the case of a double. </li><li>Whenever there is a double, the ref flips the coin again to decide who gets priority in the next double.</li></ul>', 5, '2021-09-08'),
(61, 'Sabre March', '<p><b>A</b> is attacker, <b>B</b> is defender.&nbsp;Both start in one step distance from each other, and goal for both is to land a touch. </p><p><b>A</b> starts with priority, and <b>B</b> gets the priority for a parry-riposte.</p><p><u>Win conditions for <b>A</b>:</u></p><ol><li>Make any hit with priority, or make a clean hit while not having priority.</li><li><b>B</b> crosses the back line</li></ol><p><u>Win conditions for B:</u></p><ol><li><b>A</b> stops moving forward</li><li>Make any hit with priority, or make a clean hit while not having priority.</li><li><b>A</b> swings and misses (no parry or hit)</li></ol><p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">If someone parries and no riposte lands, fence it out until someone lands a touch, with a double being a reset with no points scored.&nbsp;</span></p>', 5, '2021-08-16'),
(62, 'Poison Blade', '<p>Fencing, but any touch of <b><u>any quality</u></b> counts as a point. Any sort of 1h actions on a longsword are allowed.</p><ol><li>Only the first hit counts in the case of an afterblow. </li><li>Both players lose in the case of a simultaneous double.</li></ol>', 5, '2021-08-14'),
(63, 'La Canne', '		 			<p>Fencing, but you must chamber a strike in order to claim priority. <b>You may only score when you have priority </b>(no attacks in preparation or counterattacks).&nbsp; </p><ul><li>\"Chambering\" is defined as retracting your blade beyond 90 degree vertical, along with a backward movement of the hands</li><li>Priority ends if you hold your chambered position for too long (2 steps, or judge\'s discretion if they are standing still), or if your attack misses or is parried.&nbsp;</li><li>When a defender parries, priority immediately switches to them, and they may riposte without chambering as long as the parry and riposte are done in a fluid motion.</li><li>If both chamber, priority goes to whoever chambered first; if both chamber simultaneously, the exchange may be ruled a simultaneous and thrown out<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">).</span></li></ul>		 		', 5, '2021-08-14'),
(64, 'Zwerhaw Mixup game', '		 					 			<p>Like \"defend the wall\" but <b>A</b> may only attack with zwerhaw (cross hew). They may do mix-ups such as fehler (non-hitters, fake attacks) and duplieren (duplication, hitting behind the blade).</p><ul><li>V1: A may only attack to the head</li><li>V2: A may vary height, attacking high or low</li></ul>		 				 		', 5, '2021-06-16'),
(65, 'The Sword Grab Scramble', '<p><b>A</b> is attacker, <b>B</b> is defender, game starts with <b>A</b> grabbing <b>B</b>\'s sword between the point and the middle, <b>B</b> has both hands on the handle. </p><ol><li>Goal for <b>A</b> is a touch</li><li>Goal for <b>B</b> is to free their sword or initiate a grapple. </li></ol><p>No pommel strikes allowed.&nbsp;</p>', 5, '2021-05-19'),
(66, 'The Deadly Scissors', '<p>Both fencers start grabbing the others\' sword between the tip and the middle. Goal is to land a touch or disarm the other person\'s sword. </p><p>No pommel strikes allowed.</p>', 5, '2021-05-19'),
(67, 'The Steel Force Field', '<ol><li><b>A</b> may not move backwards, may only attack with a thrust or cut.</li><li><b>B</b> must enter distance and initiate grappling.</li></ol>', 5, '2021-05-19'),
(68, 'Stale Moves', '<p>Fencing, but once you score, hits with the move that you used to score no longer counts as valid.&nbsp;</p><p>(Adjust what counts as a \"move\" depending on your curriculum and how fast you want them to run out of options.)</p>', 5, '2021-05-19'),
(69, 'Random Priority', '<p>Third party flips a coin to decide which fencer gets priority, doesn\'t tell the fencers. Re-flip after a double or afterblow happens.&nbsp;</p>', 5, '2021-04-29'),
(70, 'Cut-to-Thrust Game', '<p>Both start in a point high guard (ie <i>vom tag</i>), only thrusts are counted as valid. Each fencer gets 2 actions before they have to reset.</p>', 5, '2021-04-18'),
(71, 'Fence Shortly', '<p>Fencing, but only strikes with the short edge are counted as valid.</p>', 5, '2021-04-18'),
(72, 'The Berthold Special', '<ol><li><b>A</b> can only attack with zwerhaws</li><li><b>B</b> must defend with a slice and follow with a hit to the head.</li></ol>', 5, '2021-04-14'),
(73, 'Shouting Window', '<p><b>A</b> starts in <i>vom tag,&nbsp;</i><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>B</b> starts in longpoint.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>A</b> must attack first, but <b>B</b> has priority until blade contact is made.&nbsp;</span></p>', 5, '2021-04-10'),
(74, 'Wave on Cliffs', '<p>Start from a bind. <b>A</b> must either cut around or try to enter into grappling. <b>B</b> must defend with a slice. </p><ol><li><b>A</b> wins by touching&nbsp;<b>B</b> or landing a hit.</li><li><b>B</b> wins by defending with a slice, or landing a slice directly on the neck from the bind.</li><li><b>B</b> may also win by landing a thrust, but are not allowed to step backwards.</li></ol><p><i>(<b>A</b> is a wave crashing and <b>B</b> is a cliff stopping the wave.)</i></p>', 5, '2021-04-09'),
(75, 'Falling Upon', '<p><b>A</b> may chose their starting guard, <b>B</b> must stay in <i>alber</i>.</p><ol><li><b>A</b> wins by making blade contact.</li><li><b>B</b> wins by making a touch.</li></ol><p>In the case of blades contacting as part of a touch the touch will have priority.</p>', 5, '2021-04-09'),
(76, 'Fallen Upon', '<p><b>A</b> starts in <i>alber</i>, <b>B</b> starts with their sword barring as if they have fallen upon it. Goal for both is to land a touch.</p><p>The game only begins after <b>A</b> leaves the bind, <b>B</b> must wait until that point before attacking.</p><p><b>A</b> gets priority in the case of a double. If fencers break distance reset to starting position.</p>', 5, '2021-04-09'),
(77, 'Bingo', '<p>Divide the body up into 6 parts. (Head, R-Arm, L-Arm, Torso, R-Leg, L-Leg)</p><p>Fight with thrusts only. (You can cut to displace a blade. Any cuts landed on the body should be ignored and not draw a hold.)</p><ol><li>You can only get points for hitting a target once. If you hit the head 6 exchanges in a row you still only get 1 point.</li><li>In the case of a double both get points. (If one hits a repeat target in the double it could still end up with their opponent getting a point and them not. Or it could be no points awarded if both hit repeat targets.)</li><li>Hitting a target you already hit does count as an exchange, even if you don\'t get points for it.</li></ol><p>Whoever has most points at the end of 6 exchanges wins.</p><p>(This can also be done allowing cut/thrust/slice/whatever scoring actions, but I don\'t quite like it as much.)</p>', 1, '2023-01-08'),
(78, 'Defend The Book', '		 					 			<p>A <i>Defend The Wall</i> variant.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Attacker <b>[</b></span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">A]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">&nbsp;performs a series of attacks against the Defender <b>[</b></span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Z]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">&nbsp;until they can no longer chain into their next attack in a continuous motion. (aka they stutter), which constitutes one \"exchange\". A match is multiple exchanges, with each student being A and&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>[</b></span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Z]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">&nbsp;an equal amount of times. (Set the cap wherever you want.)</span></p><p><b>[A]</b>&nbsp;can only use each attack once in the chain. (Define what are counted as attacks based on your schools source material.)</p><p> </p><ol><li>If&nbsp;<b>[A]</b>&nbsp;lands a hit before they break their chain (or run out of attacks they know how to do) they get a point.</li><li>If&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>[</b><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Z]</b>&nbsp;out-lasts and out-parries&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>[A]</b>&nbsp;they get a point.</span></li></ol><p>This is the simple version of the game, and can be done with any students. But the real fun is the source based component:</p><ol><li><b>[A]</b>&nbsp;may only attack with actions (in the scope of the schools source of study) they know the name of&nbsp;</li></ol><p><b>[Z]</b>&nbsp;can call on any attack that occurred during the prior exchange. (But may have to re-enact it because&nbsp;<b>[A]</b>&nbsp;won\'t remember every action in their chain.)</p><ul><li>If neither knows the name then&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>[</b></span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Z]</b>&nbsp;gets a point. (This could make the score for the set 1-1 or 0-2, depending on if&nbsp;<b>[A]</b>&nbsp;managed to land a hit or not.)</li><li>If&nbsp;<b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[A]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">&nbsp;does not know and&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>[</b></span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Z]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">&nbsp;</span><u style=\"font-size: inherit;\">does</u><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> know then&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>[</b></span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Z]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">&nbsp;instantly wins the match.</span></li></ul><p>If <b>[A]</b> and&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>[</b></span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Z]</b>&nbsp;disagree about the name then the instructor will arbitrate. Anything that makes someone want to open a book is thrown out.</p><p>(If the instructor gets annoyed because&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>[</b></span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Z]</b>&nbsp;is constantly challenging on attacks they know&nbsp;<b>[A]</b>&nbsp;knows, or constantly insisting on the wrong name, they award&nbsp;<b>[A]</b>&nbsp;victory for the match.)</p><p><br></p>		 				 		', 1, '2023-01-08'),
(79, 'Finnish Chicken\'s Beak', '<p>This is a variation on the Finnish Chicken.<br><br>Both fighters can move around and change guards freely. The only scoring actions are thrusts.</p><ul><li>You get to launch one attack*. If it hits you get 1 point, if it fails to hits your opponent gets 1 point.</li><li>If you are able to parry your opponent\'s thrust and land a thrust of your own within the next action you get 3 points.</li></ul><p>Play until someone gets 3 points.&nbsp;</p><p>* your attack is defined by the step to instigate. You can extend your sword to threaten if you want, so long as you don\'t step forward with it. In theory you can thrust at their hands as many times as you want if they are dumb to leave them extended.</p>', 1, '2023-01-12'),
(80, 'Can Opener ', '		 			<p>Pick a side, left or right. <i>This is written assuming right.</i></p><ul><li>Normal free fencing with normal scoring actions allowed.</li><li>You can only attack on the right side of the opponent\'s sword. (From the attackers point of view)</li><li>You are allowed to do one attack on the left side of the opponent\'s sword as a \"sacrifice throw\". aka if it doesn\'t hit you\'ve just lost</li></ul><p>Just because you are attacking to one side of their sword doesn\'t mean you have to attack *at* the sword. If they are in longpoint and cut/snipe to the left side of their body&nbsp; it would be on that side of the sword. You do not need to stay in contact with their sword. Being in&nbsp;<i>vom tag</i>&nbsp;has you coming down against the right side of their sword when you cut in. You can sit in <i>alber</i> in the center and chose to either come on the right with an attack that you can follow up on, or to come up on the left for your sacrifice throw attack.</p>		 		', 1, '2023-01-12'),
(81, 'Boulder Game', '		 					 			<p>A normal fencing match with simple rules:</p><ul><li>You win by getting two clean exchanges in a row.</li><li>Both doubles and afterblows* are a no-points-scored unclean exchange.</li></ul><p>This means a match could be over in two hits, or could go on for a very long time.</p><p>*With a real afterblow window that allows for a second attack to be initiated <u><i>after</i></u> someone gets hit.<br></p>		 				 		', 1, '2023-01-12'),
(82, '1 Attack, 1 Defense / Knight vs. Peasant', '<p>Game has a defender and an attacker. The attacker gets one motion with the blade in which to score a hit on the defender, the defender is only allowed one motion with the blade as defence. If a player uses their one motion they can regain their motion by breaking distance. The defender can score a point by getting chest to chest with the defender or within grappling range.<br><br>Attack Criteria: The moment the attackers blade crosses the 90 degree line it is considered an attack or the moment the momentum is arrested. Effectively this means that feints like shoulder twitches are ok, making half of a cut to one side and then pulling it and going to the other side is not.</p><p>Play this game in 5-10 minute blocks and bring people back to discuss their observations and decide if the attacker or defender has the advantage in the game.</p>', 8, '2023-01-24'),
(83, 'Step-Lunge / Two-Step', '<p>Can be played using bare hands, fencing gloves, pool noodles, socks, or with swords and gear. If using hands/gloves, target should be the upper arm/shoulder area.</p><p>Two roles: attacker and defender</p><ul><li>Attacker has up to two steps (step+lunge, step+pass) to attempt an attack and try to hit the defender.</li><li>Defender has as many steps as they need to avoid the attack. Cannot dodge with the body or use their weapon to parry.</li><li>As soon as the attacker\'s foot lands for their second step, the roles switch</li></ul><p>When a fencer hits with their attack, they score a point. Reset and play again.</p>', 14, '2023-02-14'),
(84, 'Four Openings Game', '		 			<p>		 			Fencing, but each fencer must hit all of the four openings in order, starting with upper left, then lower left, then lower right, then upper right. You can target the opening with a stab or a cut. Any cut below the arms counts as a lower opening. Proceed as normal in fencing, if a hit lands the match halts, if it is on target, that fencer now targets the next opening in the order, if it was off target then nothing is done. Hand and arm hits count as long as they are in the quadrant that is being targeted, fencer\'s and ref\'s discretion. First one to hit all four wins.</p><p>Doubles: if one side hits off target and the other hits on target, the on target hit scores. This is to prevent canceling valid hits with random doubles. If both sides hit on target, nothing is done. No afterblow.</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-filename=\"image.png\" style=\"width: 274px;\"><br></p><p>		 		</p>		 		', 5, '2023-02-19'),
(85, 'Cuts vs Thrusts', '<p>Fencing, but one side can only thrust and the other can only cut.&nbsp;</p><p>Resolve doubles however you want (right of way recommended)</p>', 5, '2023-02-19'),
(86, 'Soviet Dussack', '<p>Fencer A has a longsword boffer, B has a dussack. A\'s rules are the same as soviet foil, their only attack is a cut above the belt, if they hit they win, if they miss they lose. B may attack as many times as they want, and has priority in a double. Parrying is not allowed, if either side parries, they lose.&nbsp;</p><p>Variation: allow blade contact, but priority switches permanently for that rep as soon as blade contact is established (it does not switch back from further contact).</p>', 5, '2023-02-20'),
(87, 'Pursuit Shuffle (Symmetric Soviet Foil)', '		 			<p>Both fencers start in dominant side shoulder guard. Both can move freely, and their goals are to land a direct hit to the head. Parrying is not allowed. </p><p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">In the case of a double, priority goes to the first fencer to make the final decision to commit forward. If the swing misses, the attack is over, and the other fencer has priority for the next immediate action.</span></p>		 		', 5, '2023-02-23'),
(88, 'Circle of Circles', '		 			<p>This is a little weird to set up, and requires a bit of buy-in. (See the design, as the rules don\'t really explain it well.)</p><ul><li>Only valid cut is right long edge descending cut and right short edge (shilhau). Must alternate every time (long-short-long-etc) with the point being chambered back to at least the shoulder in between. (Running off or pulling back are both valid means of chambering.)</li><li>Only valid target is the head and the hands. Head has priority on doubles.</li><li>Each cut must be accompanied by a movement to the right. Doesn\'t mater if this is with, during, or before the cut. Just one movement per cut.</li></ul>		 		', 1, '2023-02-26'),
(89, 'Despot in the Hole', '		 					 			<p>This is an evolution of the <a href=\"https://www.gd4h.org/hga/gameInfo.php?g=34\">King in the Hole</a> game, however this time (instead of King/Peasant) we have the <b>[Despot]</b> and the <b>[Rebel]</b>. (And it\'s no longer good to be the king.)</p><ol><li>The <b>[Despot]</b> must land a clean hit on the <b>[Rebel]</b> to win.</li><li>The <b>[Rebel]</b> can win by landing a clean hit or a double where they strike to the upper opening.</li><li>In the case of a double with the <b>[Rebel]</b> striking the lower openings (torso, legs) it is a draw, and reset.</li></ol><p>Movement restrictions:</p><ul><li>Despot starts with their back to the wall. They can not <u>step</u> forward until the <b>[Rebel]</b> attacks, however can attack anything in range.</li><li>Once the <b>[Rebel]</b> attacks the <b>[Despot]</b> is allowed to move, but not run away to the side.</li><li>If measure breaks after a few sword actions reset and start again.</li></ul><p>Once the <b>[Despot]</b> loses twice in a row switch roles. Play to 10+ passes.</p>		 				 		', 1, '2023-03-12'),
(90, 'Ripping Game', '		 					 			<p>Both the <b>[Grabber]</b> and the <b>[Ripper]</b> stand stationary with swords crossed.</p><p>At some point the <b>[Grabber]</b> makes an attempt to grab the <b>[Ripper]</b>\'s blade with their off-hand <i>while keeping their sword forward</i>. The <b>[Ripper]</b> may not move until they see the <b>[Grabber]</b> make their attempt. (No feints allowed).</p><ul><li>If the <b>[Grabber]</b> manages to grab the <b>[Ripper]</b>\'s blade they win.</li><li>If the <b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[Ripper]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> manages to pull their blade free they win. The </span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[Ripper]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"> must also place their offhand on the </span><b style=\"font-size: inherit;\">[Grabber]</b><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">\'s sword hand/arm; this is to prevent them from running away as they attempt to pull their sword back.</span></li></ul><p>If the <b>[Ripper]</b> is winning more often move closer, and if the <b>[Grabber]</b> is winning more often move further apart.</p>		 				 		', 1, '2023-03-15'),
(91, 'Sock Fighting', '<p>Take a pair of knee-length socks. Roll up one of the socks and stuff it in the toe of the other to make a battle sock. Fight!<br></p><ul><li>&nbsp;Valid targets are the entire body except for the head (a sock tothe face isn\'t much fun, especially for people who wear glasses</li><li>In the case of a double or afterblow, the point goes to the fencer who started their swing first<br><br></li></ul>', 13, '2023-03-19'),
(92, 'Electric Buckler', '<ul><li>[A] has a longsword</li><li>[B] has a buckler and a sword they can \r\nhold in one hand (a longsword will do in a pinch). They must keep their \r\nbuckler fully extended at shoulder height, and the blade of their sword \r\nin contact with the edge of their buckler, at all times. They can turn \r\ntheir body in order to move the buckler, and can move their sword around\r\n the buckler.</li><li>[B] scores a point if they can touch [A]\'s sword with their buckler</li><li>[A] scores a point by landing a hit anywhere above the waist, without touching the buckler<br></li></ul><p></p>', 13, '2023-03-19'),
(93, 'Seated Epee', '<p>Both fencers are seated and must remain seated. Lifting your butt off the seat is an automatic loss, but you may lean forward or backwards. Fencers should be seated at a distance where they can barely land a thrust to the chest with two hands. Fence with only thrust allowed, target area is above the belt. One handed attacks are allowed.&nbsp;</p>', 5, '2023-03-21'),
(94, 'Grab or Going Nowhere', '<p>Arrange two benches parallel to each other, or two seats so that the fencers will be next to each other, not facing each other (see picture below). Fencers must sit so that the non-dominant leg is facing the opponent. Standing up or lifting your butt off the seat is an instant loss for that rep.&nbsp;</p><p>There are three ways to score:</p><ol><li>Hit while grappling - a grapple is defined as using your arm to manipulate the opponent\'s weapon or body so that you have immediate use of your sword and they do not have immediate use of their sword.</li><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Any hit above the belt while the opponent has only one hand on the sword.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Thrust to the upper chest while you have one hand on the handle and one hand on the blade of your sword (IE half-sword) - this scores whether the opponent has one or two hands on their sword.&nbsp;</span></li></ol>', 5, '2023-03-21'),
(95, 'Head vs Short', '<p>Asymmetric sparring game: </p><p>A can only cut with the short edge, and can target anywhere above the belt.</p><p>B can cut with either edge, but can only target the head.</p><p>Either side can thrust, but A can only thrust if it is initiated as a short edge cut (judge\'s discretion, toss this rule if it\'s too complicated).&nbsp;</p><p>Use whatever method for resolving doubles you want, or toss doubles.&nbsp;</p>', 5, '2023-03-22'),
(96, 'Sock Sabre Scissors', '<p>Fencers should be equipped with socks. Target area is anything from the waist up.</p><p>Set up a fencing piste about 4m long by 1m wide. Start fencers with their front toes on the narrow sides of the area, so there\'s 4m between both fencers.&nbsp;</p><p>When the referee calls \'fence\', both fencers must take at least a small step forward (so their foot is on the piste) and then may do as they please. Passing forward is forbidden. Priority works as follows:</p><ul><li>If only one fencer hits, they score</li><li>If both fencers hit, the one who <i>started</i>&nbsp;their lunge first scores</li><li>If one fencer lunges and does not hit, their opponent automatically scores</li><li>If one fencer retreats off the back of the piste and their opponent has not lunged, the fencer who has not left the piste scores.</li></ul><p><br></p>', 14, '2023-03-22'),
(97, 'The General Grievous', '		 			<p><b>Genera]</b> can not move their feet. They must keep their point constantly moving in circular cutting movements. (like flowdrills). They are allowed to hit any target.</p><p><b>Jedi</b>&nbsp;can move freely. They can only score by a hit to the arms, head, or thrust to the torso.</p><p>After the first sword contact (provided it wasn\'t a scoring hit) the <b>General</b>&nbsp;can now move their sword and feet freely, and they have priority.</p><p><b>General</b>&nbsp;can also attempt a \"sacrifice throw\" at any time: to land a hit with a thrust and step forward. But if the thrust fails to hit they lose.</p><p>-----------------------</p><p><u>Edge cases/doubles</u>: In most cases doubles will resolve with priority to the <b>General</b>. Such as if the <b>Jedi</b> attacks and fails to cover one of the attacks that is already swinging towards them. However if the <b>General</b> ignores the attack of the <b>Jedi</b> and changes their cutting line to an opening their weren\'t originally targeting then they should lose their priority. As a coach call this as it seems to make sense.<br></p>		 		', 1, '2023-04-01'),
(98, 'Wight of Ray', '<p>Normal fencing match in a well defined ring area. No afterblows, but a long window for doubles.</p><p>If there is a double hit it should be arbitrated based on the following priority:</p><ol><li>Opponent leaves ring (auto-win, no matter who hits)</li><li>Hit any target while backing up</li><li>Hit deep target while standing still</li><li>Hit deep while moving forward, or shallow while standing still.</li></ol><p>Works better with a relatively small ring size.</p>', 1, '2023-05-02'),
(99, 'Shut It Down', '<p>Both fighters start in <i>vom tag</i> and can move freely around a marked ring. </p><p>The <b>[Vor]</b> fighter must engage with a direct attack to the head. Once they have engaged they can not stop (or pause) cutting (and are not allowed to take hands off their sword to engage in a grapple). They win by landing a cut above the waist.</p><p>The <b>[Nach]</b> fighter can win by either having one of the <b>[Vor]</b>\'s fighters not hit anything (including their sword), or engaging in a grapple that ties up the <b>[Vor]</b>\'s ability to attack.</p>', 1, '2023-05-04'),
(100, 'Wrestling on the March', '<p>Standard marching pattern. Target zone is waist up.</p><p>Attacker wins on:</p><ul><li>Hitting the defender (including any double)</li><li>The defender retreating past the back line</li></ul><p>Defender wins on:</p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">Attacker stepping back</span></li><li>Making a clean hit with their sword</li><li>Touching the attacker\'s torso with their hand</li></ul><p>Note: it\'s been a while since I played this, you may also need to allow the defender to win on a missed or parried attack from the attacker.&nbsp;</p>', 14, '2023-05-06'),
(101, 'Finnish Bull', '		 			<p><b>IMPORTANT: This can escalate and be a safety concern, please see Design Notes</b></p><p>Starts with the same framework as Finnish Chicken. Both in right <i>vom tag</i>, and the only attack allowed is a direct attack to the head from the right. Unlike the Finnish Chicken you are allowed, and expected, to defend with an attack to the head of your own.</p><ul><li>Win: You attack hits the head and they do not hit you.</li><li>Win: If an opponent\'s attack misses or falls short. This also includes feints you don\'t take action with your sword against.</li><li>Win: If you feint an attack and they parry rather than hitting you.</li><li>Double hits to the head, or attacks that cancel each other out, are a draw.</li></ul>		 		', 1, '2023-06-01'),
(102, 'Head-Leg-Parry, Direct Attack', '<p>This is a variation on the Direct Attack game. The attacker and defender are both in vom tag, and the defender cannot move until the attacker instigates.</p><p>The \"attacker\" can chose one of three options:</p><ol><li>Direct attack to the head</li><li>Direct attack to the leg</li><li>Step forward with a parry</li></ol><p>The \"defender\" can respond with one of the three options:</p><ol><li>Parry</li><li>Counterattack to the head</li><li>Back up and don\'t extend sword</li></ol><p>Outcomes are decided as:</p><ul><li>Priority #1: Should the defender swing into a parry of the attacker, the attacker wins</li><li>Priority #2: Should the attacker not hit, the defender wins</li><li>Priority #3: Should the defender hit while the attacker is going for the leg, the defender wins.</li><li>Priority #4: Should there be a double while the attacker is attacking the head, the attacker wins.</li></ul><p><br></p><p>The game can be done as a standard direct attack with both stationary, but it is better to tell the attacker to start back from the starting line, and they much approach and attack without stopping. This creates pressure on their decision making and also adds information on how they approach the line into the game.</p><div><br></div>', 1, '2023-06-17'),
(103, 'Head-Leg-Parry, Ratchet', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Both fighters start in <i>vom tag</i>, and there are no roles. They\r\nboth must approach each other and are not allowed to stop moving forward until\r\nthey commit to an action. (More at the bottom)</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">To engage they can chose the following options:<o:p></o:p></p><ul><li>Direct attack to the head</li><li>Direct attack to the leg</li><li>Step forward with a parry</li><li>Dont engage with sword.</li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">You can win by:</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p></o:p></p><ul><li>Having someone swing into your parry. (If they dont attack\r\ninto it and wait, you lose)</li><li>Hitting someone in the head/shoulders without being hit in\r\nthe <u style=\"font-size: inherit;\">head/shoulders</u><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">.</span></li><li>Hitting someone in the leg without being hit.</li><li>Having someone miss (you are not allowed to back up on the defense,\r\nhowever you can avoid to the side and/or void the leg)</li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p></o:p></p>', 1, '2023-06-17');
